### Ticketing Reactive - API Requests Collection
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or any tool that supports .http files

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1
@contentType = application/json

# ─── 1. EVENTS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a new event (100 tickets capacity)
# @name createEvent
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Coldplay - Music of the Spheres World Tour",
  "date": "2026-09-15T20:00:00",
  "venue": "Estadio El Campin - Bogotá",
  "totalCapacity": 100
}

### Get event ID from create response
@eventId = {{createEvent.response.body.eventId}}

---

### List all events with available tickets
GET {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

---

### Get real-time availability for event
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}/availability
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

---

# ─── 2. ORDERS (Purchase Flow) ────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a purchase order (reserve 2 tickets)
# @name createOrder
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "eventId": "{{eventId}}",
  "userId": "user-jhoan-123",
  "quantity": 2
}

### Get order ID from response
@orderId = {{createOrder.response.body.orderId}}

---

### Query order status (poll until CONFIRMED)
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/{{orderId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

---

# ─── 3. ERROR CASES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Buy when not enough tickets (conflict test)
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "eventId": "{{eventId}}",
  "userId": "user-flood-test",
  "quantity": 200
}

---

### Get non-existent event availability (404 test)
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/non-existent-id/availability
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

---

### Get non-existent order status (404 test)
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/non-existent-order-id
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

---

### Validate max quantity constraint (should fail: max 10)
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "eventId": "{{eventId}}",
  "userId": "user-greedy",
  "quantity": 15
}
